Afzal Khan is accused of conning a string of customers and financial firms at a motor dealership he ran in the US .
Fraudster opened the Emporio Motor Group in New Jersey in 2013 and maintained a high profile .
He has now been placed on the FBI's Most Wanted list over claims he has fled the country and has offered a $20,000 reward for information leading to his arrest .
If convicted, he could face 20 years in prison and a multi-million dollar fine .